## Machine-time comparison (excluding human dialog latency)
standard Run (run E): 3.16 build + 0.07 dialog-post + 0.56 install-commit + 0.37 launch = ~4.2s
                      + THREE interactive dialogs (installer confirm, Play Protect, launch prompt)
                      + app restarts cold (state lost)
standard Run build phase across runs with a real edit: 2.88 / 3.16 / 4.78s (median 3.16s)
quick build same class: p50 0.97s build, ~1.05-1.1s wall edit->deployed, ZERO dialogs,
                      no reinstall, activity recreate only

ratio (machine-only, minimal-size project): 4.2 / 1.07 = 3.9x
ratio (with 1s/dialog fast human handling, 3 dialogs): 7.2 / 1.07 = 6.7x
ratio (build-phase only): 3.16 / 0.97 = 3.3x

NOTE: LemonadeStand is a minimal single-module app - the standard path's Gradle
overhead is at its floor here. Larger corpus apps widen the gap (device matrix:
fanout const-change quick compile 1.85s vs a full Gradle recompile+package+install
of a 34-class module). Play Protect re-prompts on EVERY install while unscanned:
the "one-time popup" framing in B1 is optimistic on Play-Protect-enabled devices.
